reviews.text: Nice old retro station. Toilets are a bit dirty so a bit of a clean up and then it'll be good. I like the atmosphere in these old station buildings

For a town in Surrey this size, the train service is dire -but that's the fault of those who built the railways. As the local squaddies say, the trains here go from Arse-cot to All-the-sh*t and back. If you want to get out into the wider world, catch the number 1 bus to Farnborough Main station (18 minutes) and then your train there.
Good range of shops. Love the second hand/upcycled furniture shops

Even with the stations platform being lengthened to accommodate for 8 car trains. It is still a run down station which needs to be renewed. The station ticket office and the internal part of the station is only open till the afternoon. After that there is no access to the main building. So the ticket machines are the only way to get a ticket when it's closed. It should really be open untill the evening. Since slot of people have questions about there journey. Also with the main building being closed. It only offers weather cover for one platform. And there is no toilet access when it's closed. So the closest option is inside The Mall.
It's run down and needing a face-lift. Staff were helpful tho. It's a shame no money seems to have been spent here for years. Boards on every platform with clear information.
